Just some convenient commands to test new image interactively

Base image from Docker: https://hub.docker.com/r/_/centos/
$ singularity pull --name CentOS.simg docker://centos:centos7

sudo but no "--writable" allows us to install new libraries without changing the *.simg files
$ sudo singularity shell CentOS.simg

Enable coloring inside container
$ alias ls="ls --color=auto"

Inside container, can install libraries without using sudo
$ yum install -y which wget

Can install f2py (needed by MAPL) without using Anaconda
$ yum install -y numpy-f2py

